docs.lead_paragraph: Last spring, on the morning of her 82d birthday, Dr. May Edward Chinn was back in practice. Because of an illness, she had closed her office in 1977, fearing that she was leaving medicine for good. But on April 15, 1978, as a sort of birthday present to herself, she renewed her personal war against cancer.
docs.abstract: George Davis article on 83-yr-old Dr May Edward Chinn, who was 1st black woman graduate of Bellevue Hospital Medical Coll, 1st black woman intern at Harlem Hospital, and for many yrs the only black female dr in Harlem; notes Chinn is still practicing medicine, despite bout with cancer; illus (L)
